    "recap_headline": "West Virginia University",
    "recap_text": "MORGANTOWN, W.Va.\u00a0\u2013\u00a0The West Virginia University baseball team defeated Maryland, 10-3, Tuesday afternoon at Kendrick Family Ballpark. The Mountaineers improve to 11-3 while the Terrapins fall to 10-6.\nWest Virginia pitchers combined to throw eight shutout innings before Maryland put up a couple of runs in the ninth. Sophomore\nDavid Hagen\nthrew an inning with two strikeouts before leaving due to injury in the second. Senior\nCarson Estridge\ntossed 3.0 scoreless while graduate student\nIan Korn\nretired all six batters he faced. Sophomores\nMac Stiffler\nand\nBryant Yoak\neach recorded scoreless outings as well.\nAt the plate, senior\nPaul Schoenfeld\nhad three hits, including a triple, and two RBI while sophomore\nGavin Kelly\nreached base three times, drove in two runs and scored two runs. Senior\nMatthew Graveline\nalso finished the day with two RBI.\nSchoenfeld got the scoring started in the first with an RBI single before a productive groundout from Graveline pushed across another run.\nIn the second, WVU pushed four runs across, getting an RBI single from junior\nTyrus Hall\nbefore a run came home on a double-steal attempt. Schoenfeld followed with an RBI triple who then scored on a single by Graveline.\nIn the third, Kelly knocked in two runs with a single. The Mountaineers then added two more runs in the fourth on singles by senior\nBrock Wills\nand junior\nArmani Guzman\n.\nWest Virginia has now beaten the Terrapins six consecutive times dating back to 2017.\nThe Mountaineers begin Big 12 play this weekend when they travel to Baylor. First pitch from Baylor Ballpark in Waco, Texas is set for 7:30 p.m.\nFor more information on the Mountaineers, follow @WVUBaseball on\nTwitter\n,\nFacebook\n, and\nInstagram\n."
